{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840991443,"sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","part":{"id":"prt_d785f143c001CXfB5Z7PQ0gUGO","messageID":"msg_d785ef42e001V2hdY9060Qd9SH","sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_beff54bbaa4f4c368afc74cc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003: CRD Shared Types & Constants\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal defines shared types and constants for the `pkg/apis` module to be used across CRDs in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Centralize common type definitions** - Avoid duplication of types like `ResourceQuota`, `NetworkPolicy`, and lifecycle hooks across multiple CRDs\n8: 2. **Establish naming conventions** - Consistent naming for phases, conditions, and resource types\n9: 3. **Provide reusable validation utilities** - Shared validation functions for common fields\n10: 4. **Enable code generation consistency** - Ensure generated client-go code follows consistent patterns\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n15: **Language:** Go  \n16: **Size:** S\n17: \n18: This AR covers:\n19: \n20: - **In scope:**\n21:   - Common type definitions in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n22:   - Constant definitions for phases and condition types\n23:   - Shared validation utilities\n24:   - Documentation of patterns for future CRDs\n25: \n26: - **Out of scope:**\n27:   - Changes to existing CRD structures (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n28:   - Client-go code generation changes\n29:   - Controller logic modifications\n30: \n31: ## Current State Analysis\n32: \n33: ### Existing Shared Types\n34: \n35: The codebase already has several types that could be considered \"shared\":\n36: \n37: 1. **`ResourceQuota`** (`types.go:80-90`) - CPU, Memory, Storage limits\n38: 2. **`NetworkPolicy`** / `NetworkRule` (`types.go:102-110`) - Network access rules\n39: 3. **`LifecycleHook`** (`types.go:115-123`) - PreStart/PostStop callbacks\n40: 4. **`ContainerSpec`** (`types.go:125-143`) - Container configuration\n41: 5. **`CodeInterpreterSpec`** (`types.go:79-90`) - Embedded interpreter config\n42: \n43: ### Existing Constants\n44: \n45: 1. **AgentRuntimePhase** constants (`types.go:26-36`):\n46:    - `AgentRuntimePhasePending`\n47:    - `AgentRuntimePhaseRunning`\n48:    - `AgentRuntimePhaseFailed`\n49:    - `AgentRuntimePhaseTerminating`\n50: \n51: 2. **AgentRuntimeConditionType** constants (`types.go:38-48`):\n52:    - `AgentRuntimeConditionReady`\n53:    - `AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated`\n54:    - `AgentRuntimeConditionCodeInterpreterReady`\n55: \n56: 3. **AgentRuntimeCondition** struct (`types.go:50-64`) - Reusable condition pattern\n57: \n58: ### Issues Identified\n59: \n60: 1. **Naming inconsistency**: Types are prefixed with `AgentRuntime` but could be more generic\n61: 2. **No shared validation**: Validation logic in `validation.go:171` for `CodeInterpreter` is specific to that type\n62: 3. **No documentation**: No clear guidelines on which types should be shared vs. CRD-specific\n63: 4. **Tight coupling**: `CodeInterpreterSpec` is embedded in `AgentRuntimeSpec` but may need to be standalone\n64: \n65: ## Proposed Changes\n66: \n67: ### 1. Type Categorization\n68: \n69: Introduce clear categorization for types:\n70: \n71: ```\n72: pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n73: ├── types_common.go      # Shared types (ResourceQuota, NetworkPolicy, etc.)\n74: ├── types_agentruntime.go  # AgentRuntime-specific types\n75: └── types_codeinterpreter.go # CodeInterpreter-specific types (if needed)\n76: ```\n77: \n78: **Rationale:** Improves discoverability and makes it clear which types are intended for reuse.\n79: \n80: ### 2. Standardize Type Naming\n81: \n82: Current naming is already consistent with Kubernetes conventions:\n83: - All types use PascalCase\n84: - Related types share prefixes (e.g., `AgentRuntimePhase`, `AgentRuntimeCondition`)\n85: - Embedded structs use descriptive names (`CodeInterpreterSpec`, not just `CodeInterpreter`)\n86: \n87: **No changes needed** - current naming follows Kubernetes API conventions.\n88: \n89: ### 3. Extract Shared Validation\n90: \n91: Create reusable validation functions in `validation.go`:\n92: \n93: ```go\n94: // ValidateResourceQuota validates resource quota fields\n95: func ValidateResourceQuota(quota *ResourceQuota, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n96: \n97: // ValidateNetworkPolicy validates network policy configuration\n98: func ValidateNetworkPolicy(policy *NetworkPolicy, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n99: \n100: // ValidateContainerSpec validates container specification\n101: func ValidateContainerSpec(spec *ContainerSpec, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n102: ```\n103: \n104: **Impact:** Reduces code duplication when adding new CRDs that use these types.\n105: \n106: ### 4. Document Type Usage Patterns\n107: \n108: Add package-level documentation in `doc.go`:\n109: \n110: ```go\n111: // Package v1alpha1 defines the AgentCube runtime API types.\n112: //\n113: // Shared Types:\n114: // Types without AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter prefix are intended for reuse:\n115: // - ResourceQuota: Resource limits and requests\n116: // - NetworkPolicy/NetworkRule: Network access control\n117: // - LifecycleHook: Lifecycle callbacks\n118: // - ContainerSpec: Container configuration\n119: //\n120: // CRD-Specific Types:\n121: // Types prefixed with AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter are specific\n122: // to those CRDs and should not be assumed reusable.\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### 5. Consider Future CRD Compatibility\n126: \n127: For types that may be used by multiple CRDs:\n128: \n129: **Option A: Keep in v1alpha1 package**\n130: - Simple, no import cycles\n131: - All types in one place\n132: - Risk: Package becomes too large\n133: \n134: **Option B: Extract to `pkg/apis/common`**\n135: - Clearer separation\n136: - Can be imported by multiple API groups\n137: - Risk: Import cycles with scheme registration\n138: \n139: **Recommendation:** Use Option A for now (keep all in `v1alpha1`). Revisit Option B when adding a second API group (e.g., `session.agentcube.volcano.sh`).\n140: \n141: ## Impact Analysis\n142: \n143: ### Files to Modify\n144: \n145: | File | Changes | Impact |\n146: |------|---------|--------|\n147: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Add type usage documentation | Low - documentation only |\n148: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go` | Extract shared validation functions | Medium - affects validation tests |\n149: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Add comments marking shared types | Low - backward compatible |\n150: \n151: ### Backward Compatibility\n152: \n153: All changes are **backward compatible**:\n154: - No existing type signatures change\n155: - Existing CRDs continue to work\n156: - Generated client-go code is unaffected\n157: \n158: ### Testing Impact\n159: \n160: - Existing unit tests continue to pass\n161: - May add tests for shared validation functions\n162: - No integration test changes needed\n163: \n164: ## Alternatives Considered\n165: \n166: ### Alternative 1: Separate Common Package\n167: \n168: Create `pkg/apis/common/types.go` for shared types.\n169: \n170: **Pros:**\n171: - Clear separation of concerns\n172: - Can be imported by multiple API groups\n173: \n174: **Cons:**\n175: - Import cycles with scheme registration\n176: - Over-engineering for single API group\n177: - More complex code generation setup\n178: \n179: **Decision:** Defer until we have multiple API groups.\n180: \n181: ### Alternative 2: Use Kubernetes Core Types\n182: \n183: Replace `ResourceQuota` with `corev1.ResourceRequirements`.\n184: \n185: **Pros:**\n186: - Standard Kubernetes types\n187: - Better integration with ecosystem tools\n188: \n189: **Cons:**\n190: - `corev1.ResourceRequirements` is more complex than needed\n191: - Loses semantic clarity (our `ResourceQuota` has specific meaning)\n192: - Breaking change for existing CRDs\n193: \n194: **Decision:** Keep custom `ResourceQuota` but document mapping to core types.\n195: \n196: ### Alternative 3: Generate Types from Schema\n197: \n198: Use kube-builder markers to generate types from a schema definition.\n199: \n200: **Pros:**\n201: - Single source of truth\n202: - Automatic validation generation\n203: \n204: **Cons:**\n205: - Significant refactoring effort\n206: - Loss of Go type safety during development\n207: - Complex toolchain setup\n208: \n209: **Decision:** Not justified for current project size.\n210: \n211: ## Implementation Checklist\n212: \n213: - [ ] Add package-level documentation in `doc.go`\n214: - [ ] Add comments to shared types in `types.go`\n215: - [ ] Extract shared validation functions in `validation.go`\n216: - [ ] Update validation tests for extracted functions\n217: - [ ] Document patterns in `deployment/client-go.md`\n218: \n219: ## Future Considerations\n220: \n221: 1. **Multiple API Groups**: When adding `session.agentcube.volcano.sh`, reconsider shared type location\n222: 2. **Webhook Validation**: Move validation to admission webhooks for better error messages\n223: 3. **Defaulting Webhooks**: Consider separate defaulting functions for shared types\n224: 4. **Conversion Webhooks**: Plan for v1alpha1 → v1beta1 migration path\n225: \n226: ## References\n227: \n228: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n229: - [Kube-builder Book](https://book.kubebuilder.io/)\n230: - Deployment spec: `deployment/spec.md`\n231: - Client-go documentation: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 231 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003: CRD Shared Types & Constants\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal defines shared types and constants for the `pkg/apis` module to be used across CRDs in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Centralize common type definitions** - Avoid duplication of types like `ResourceQuota`, `NetworkPolicy`, and lifecycle hooks across multiple CRDs\n2. **Establish naming conventions** - Consistent naming for phases, conditions, and resource types\n3. **Provide reusable validation utilities** - Shared validation functions for common fields\n4. **Enable code generation consistency** - Ensure generated client-go code follows consistent patterns\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840991432,"end":1775840991441}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840991448,"sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","part":{"id":"prt_d785f08ff0012mV960lGqK20GQ","messageID":"msg_d785ef42e001V2hdY9060Qd9SH","sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0709d7b7c2f84288a9079433","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage AI agent runtime configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing the foundation for sandbox orchestration and lifecycle management.\n6: \n7: The `AgentRuntime` resource represents a configurable agent execution environment with support for:\n8: - Code interpreter attachment\n9: - Resource quotas (CPU, memory, storage)\n10: - Network policies and egress rules\n11: - Lifecycle hooks (preStart, postStop)\n12: - Status tracking (phase, conditions, sandbox reference)\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n17: **API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n18: **Kind:** `AgentRuntime` (namespaced)  \n19: **Size:** S\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: 1. **Type Definitions** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`)\n24:    - `AgentRuntime` - main resource struct\n25:    - `AgentRuntimeSpec` - desired state specification\n26:    - `AgentRuntimeStatus` - observed state status\n27:    - `CodeInterpreterSpec` - embedded code interpreter configuration\n28:    - `ResourceQuota` - sandbox resource limits\n29:    - `NetworkPolicy` - egress/ingress rules\n30:    - `LifecycleHook` - preStart/postStop callbacks\n31:    - `AgentRuntimePhase` - lifecycle phase enum\n32:    - `AgentRuntimeCondition` - status conditions\n33: \n34: 2. **API Registration** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`)\n35:    - `SchemeGroupVersion` definition\n36:    - `SchemeBuilder` registration\n37:    - `AddToScheme` function\n38:    - `Resource` and `Kind` helpers\n39: \n40: 3. **CRD Manifest** (`manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`)\n41:    - OpenAPI v3 schema validation\n42:    - Subresources: `/status`, `/scale` (if needed)\n43:    - AdditionalPrinterColumns for kubectl output\n44:    - Conversion webhook placeholders (future)\n45: \n46: 4. **Defaulting & Validation** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/defaults.go`, `validation.go`)\n47:    - `SetDefaults_AgentRuntime` - default values\n48:    - `ValidateAgentRuntime` - spec validation rules\n49:    - `ValidateAgentRuntimeStatusUpdate` - status update validation\n50: \n51: 5. **Utility Functions**\n52:    - Phase transition helpers\n53:    - Condition management (GetCondition, SetCondition, RemoveCondition)\n54:    - Deep copy utilities (via code generation)\n55: \n56: ### Out of Scope\n57: \n58: - Controller implementation (covered by AR-002)\n59: - Webhook admission controllers (deferred to AR-010)\n60: - Conversion webhooks for version upgrades (deferred)\n61: - CLI commands for AgentRuntime (Python SDK task)\n62: \n63: ## Impact Analysis\n64: \n65: ### Dependencies\n66: \n67: | Dependency | Type | Reason |\n68: |------------|------|--------|\n69: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required | MetaV1 types, runtime.Object, schema |\n70: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | ResourceList, PodSecurityContext, EnvVar |\n71: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Generated | Clientset, listers, informers (via `make gen-client`) |\n72: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Module | API group registration |\n73: \n74: ### Downstream Consumers\n75: \n76: 1. **Controller (AR-002)**: Watches `AgentRuntime` resources, reconciles to create sandbox pods\n77: 2. **Router**: Reads `AgentRuntime` status to route traffic to active sandboxes\n78: 3. **Python SDK**: Provides high-level API for creating/managing AgentRuntime resources\n79: 4. **CLI Tool**: Exposes `agentcube runtime create/get/list/delete` commands\n80: 5. **Helm Chart**: Ships CRD manifest for cluster installation\n81: \n82: ### Breaking Changes\n83: \n84: None - this is the initial definition of the API.\n85: \n86: ### Migration Path\n87: \n88: Not applicable for initial implementation. Future version migrations (v1alpha2, v1beta1) will require:\n89: - Conversion webhook implementation\n90: - Storage version bumps\n91: - helm chart upgrade hooks\n92: \n93: ## Alternatives Considered\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 1: Use Deployment + ConfigMap instead of CRD\n96: \n97: **Approach:** Represent agent runtimes as standard Kubernetes Deployments with configuration in ConfigMaps.\n98: \n99: **Pros:**\n100: - No CRD complexity or controller required\n101: - Leverages built-in Kubernetes primitives\n102: - Simpler RBAC story\n103: \n104: **Cons:**\n105: - Loses semantic meaning (Deployment is generic)\n106: - Complex validation logic in admission webhooks\n107: - Status reporting requires custom annotations\n108: - Harder to query/filter agent-specific resources\n109: - No custom subresources (e.g., `/exec`, `/logs` future extensions)\n110: \n111: **Decision:** Rejected. CRD provides better abstraction, type safety, and extensibility for AgentCube semantics.\n112: \n113: ### Alternative 2: Single monolithic AgentRuntime CRD with all features\n114: \n115: **Approach:** Include all possible configuration options (networking, storage, auth, scheduling) in one large spec.\n116: \n117: **Pros:**\n118: - One resource to rule them all\n119: - Maximum flexibility for users\n120: \n121: **Cons:**\n122: - High cognitive load for simple use cases\n123: - Validation complexity\n124: - Harder to evolve individual aspects\n125: - Violates separation of concerns\n126: \n127: **Decision:** Rejected. Prefer composable design with `CodeInterpreter` as separate but related resource. Core `AgentRuntime` focuses on execution environment; advanced features (distributed training, multi-agent orchestration) can be future extensions.\n128: \n129: ### Alternative 3: Use Pod-level primitives (PodTemplate) directly\n130: \n131: **Approach:** Embed raw PodTemplateSpec in AgentRuntime spec.\n132: \n133: **Pros:**\n134: - Full Kubernetes pod configuration available\n135: - No translation layer needed\n136: \n137: **Cons:**\n138: - Exposes low-level K8s details to end users\n139: - Harder to enforce platform policies\n140: - Breaks abstraction if K8s pod spec changes\n141: \n142: **Decision:** Partially adopted. AgentRuntimeSpec contains a simplified `Container` subset (image, env, resources) rather than full PodSpec, with controller translating to Pod internals. This balances flexibility with abstraction.\n143: \n144: ## Implementation Plan\n145: \n146: 1. **Scaffold directory structure**\n147:    - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n148:    - `pkg/apis/runtime/register.go` (group registration)\n149: \n150: 2. **Define Go types** (`types.go`)\n151:    - Core structs with JSON tags\n152:    - Phase enum and conditions\n153:    - Embedded CodeInterpreterSpec\n154: \n155: 3. **Implement registration** (`register.go`)\n156:    - SchemeGroupVersion constants\n157:    - SchemeBuilder wiring\n158: \n159: 4. **Add defaults and validation**\n160:    - `defaults.go`: SetDefaults_AgentRuntime\n161:    - `validation.go`: ValidateAgentRuntime\n162: \n163: 5. **Generate CRD manifest**\n164:    - Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen)\n165:    - Place in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n166: \n167: 6. **Generate client code**\n168:    - Run `make gen-client` (code-generator)\n169:    - Produces clientset, listers, informers\n170: \n171: 7. **Write unit tests**\n172:    - Type round-trip serialization\n173:    - Defaulting behavior\n174:    - Validation rules\n175: \n176: ## Success Criteria\n177: \n178: - [ ] `AgentRuntime` CRD installs via Helm chart\n179: - [ ] `kubectl apply -f agentruntime.yaml` succeeds\n180: - [ ] `kubectl get agentruntime` shows custom columns\n181: - [ ] Go client can create/get/update AgentRuntime\n182: - [ ] Spec validation rejects invalid resources\n183: - [ ] Defaulting applies expected values\n184: - [ ] Code generation produces compilable client-go code\n185: \n186: ## References\n187: \n188: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n189: - [Controller Tools CRD Generation](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n190: - [Kubernetes Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n191: - AgentCube deployment spec: `deployment/spec.md`\n192: - Client-go reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 192 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage AI agent runtime configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing the foundation for sandbox orchestration and lifecycle management.\n\nThe `AgentRuntime` resource represents a configurable agent execution environment with support for:\n- Code interpreter attachment\n- Resource quotas (CPU, memory, storage)\n- Network policies and egress rules\n- Lifecycle hooks (preStart, postStop)\n- Status tracking (phase, conditions, sandbox reference)\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n**Kind:** `AgentRuntime` (namespaced)  \n**Size:** S\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840991426,"end":1775840991446}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840991452,"sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","part":{"id":"prt_d785f0e9f0010B71JprVeOJ9MD","messageID":"msg_d785ef42e001V2hdY9060Qd9SH","sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1bc9f111a81e465d84b76654","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage code interpreter configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing isolated kernel environments for AI agent code execution.\n6: \n7: The `CodeInterpreter` resource represents a configurable code execution environment with support for:\n8: - Multiple kernel languages (Python, R, Julia, etc.)\n9: - Session management and lifecycle\n10: - Security policies (package allowlists, operation restrictions)\n11: - Resource quotas (CPU, memory per session)\n12: - Status tracking (phase, conditions, active sessions)\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n17: **API Group:** `codeinterpreter.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n18: **Kind:** `CodeInterpreter` (namespaced)  \n19: **Size:** S\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: 1. **Type Definitions** (`pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/types.go`)\n24:    - `CodeInterpreter` - main resource struct\n25:    - `CodeInterpreterSpec` - desired state specification\n26:    - `CodeInterpreterStatus` - observed state status\n27:    - `KernelSpec` - kernel configuration (language, image, resources)\n28:    - `SessionConfig` - session timeout and limits\n29:    - `SecurityPolicy` - package allowlists and operation restrictions\n30:    - `CodeInterpreterPhase` - lifecycle phase enum\n31:    - `CodeInterpreterCondition` - status conditions\n32: \n33: 2. **API Registration** (`pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/register.go`)\n34:    - `SchemeGroupVersion` definition\n35:    - `SchemeBuilder` registration\n36:    - `AddToScheme` function\n37:    - `Resource` and `Kind` helpers\n38: \n39: 3. **CRD Manifest** (`manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml`)\n40:    - OpenAPI v3 schema validation\n41:    - Subresources: `/status`\n42:    - AdditionalPrinterColumns for kubectl output\n43:    - Conversion webhook placeholders (future)\n44: \n45: 4. **Defaulting & Validation** (`pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/defaults.go`, `validation.go`)\n46:    - `SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter` - default values\n47:    - `ValidateCodeInterpreter` - spec validation rules\n48:    - `ValidateCodeInterpreterStatusUpdate` - status update validation\n49: \n50: 5. **Utility Functions**\n51:    - Phase transition helpers\n52:    - Condition management (GetCondition, SetCondition, RemoveCondition)\n53:    - Deep copy utilities (via code generation)\n54: \n55: ### Out of Scope\n56: \n57: - Controller implementation (deferred to AR-003)\n58: - Kernel image building and management (infrastructure task)\n59: - Session WebSocket proxying (deferred to router component)\n60: - Python SDK bindings (Python SDK task)\n61: \n62: ## Impact Analysis\n63: \n64: ### Dependencies\n65: \n66: | Dependency | Type | Reason |\n67: |------------|------|--------|\n68: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required | MetaV1 types, runtime.Object, schema |\n69: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | ResourceList, SecurityContext, EnvVar |\n70: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Generated | Clientset, listers, informers (via `make gen-client`) |\n71: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Module | API group registration |\n72: \n73: ### Downstream Consumers\n74: \n75: 1. **Controller (AR-003)**: Watches `CodeInterpreter` resources, reconciles to create kernel pods\n76: 2. **AgentRuntime (AR-001)**: References `CodeInterpreter` for agent code execution capability\n77: 3. **Router**: Manages WebSocket connections to active interpreter sessions\n78: 4. **Python SDK**: Provides high-level API for creating/managing CodeInterpreter resources\n79: 5. **CLI Tool**: Exposes `agentcube interpreter create/get/list/delete` commands\n80: 6. **Helm Chart**: Ships CRD manifest for cluster installation\n81: \n82: ### Breaking Changes\n83: \n84: None - this is the initial definition of the API.\n85: \n86: ### Migration Path\n87: \n88: Not applicable for initial implementation. Future version migrations (v1alpha2, v1beta1) will require:\n89: - Conversion webhook implementation\n90: - Storage version bumps\n91: - Helm chart upgrade hooks\n92: \n93: ## Alternatives Considered\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 1: Embed CodeInterpreter config in AgentRuntime\n96: \n97: **Approach:** Include code interpreter configuration as a nested field within `AgentRuntime` spec.\n98: \n99: **Pros:**\n100: - Single resource to manage\n101: - Simpler deployment model\n102: - No additional CRD overhead\n103: \n104: **Cons:**\n105: - Couples agent lifecycle with interpreter lifecycle\n106: - Cannot share interpreters across agents\n107: - Harder to scale interpreters independently\n108: - Limits multi-language support per agent\n109: \n110: **Decision:** Rejected. Separating concerns allows interpreters to be managed, scaled, and versioned independently. Multiple agents can reference the same interpreter, and agents can switch interpreters without recreation.\n111: \n112: ### Alternative 2: Use Jupyter kernel gateway directly\n113: \n114: **Approach:** Deploy Jupyter Kernel Gateway as a standard Deployment and manage kernels via REST API.\n115: \n116: **Pros:**\n117: - Leverages existing Jupyter ecosystem\n118: - Mature kernel management\n119: - Built-in WebSocket support\n120: \n121: **Cons:**\n122: - No Kubernetes-native resource model\n123: - Custom integration required for lifecycle management\n124: - Harder to enforce cluster-wide policies\n125: - No status reporting to Kubernetes API\n126: \n127: **Decision:** Partially adopted. CodeInterpreter CRD represents the desired state; controller will create/manage Jupyter Kernel Gateway deployments based on CRD spec. This combines K8s-native abstraction with proven kernel technology.\n128: \n129: ### Alternative 3: One CodeInterpreter per language\n130: \n131: **Approach:** Create separate CRDs for PythonInterpreter, RInterpreter, JuliaInterpreter, etc.\n132: \n133: **Pros:**\n134: - Language-specific validation rules\n135: - Clear separation of concerns\n136: - Simpler schemas per CRD\n137: \n138: **Cons:**\n139: - CRD proliferation\n140: - Duplicate code across CRDs\n141: - Harder to support polyglot agents\n142: - More complex client code\n143: \n144: **Decision:** Rejected. Single `CodeInterpreter` CRD with `KernelSpec.language` field provides flexibility while maintaining simplicity. Validation rules can branch on language field.\n145: \n146: ## Implementation Plan\n147: \n148: 1. **Scaffold directory structure**\n149:    - `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/`\n150:    - `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/register.go` (group registration)\n151: \n152: 2. **Define Go types** (`types.go`)\n153:    - Core structs with JSON tags\n154:    - Phase enum and conditions\n155:    - KernelSpec and SecurityPolicy\n156: \n157: 3. **Implement registration** (`register.go`)\n158:    - SchemeGroupVersion constants\n159:    - SchemeBuilder wiring\n160: \n161: 4. **Add defaults and validation**\n162:    - `defaults.go`: SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter\n163:    - `validation.go`: ValidateCodeInterpreter\n164: \n165: 5. **Generate CRD manifest**\n166:    - Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen)\n167:    - Place in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n168: \n169: 6. **Generate client code**\n170:    - Run `make gen-client` (code-generator)\n171:    - Produces clientset, listers, informers\n172: \n173: 7. **Write unit tests**\n174:    - Type round-trip serialization\n175:    - Defaulting behavior\n176:    - Validation rules\n177: \n178: ## Success Criteria\n179: \n180: - [ ] `CodeInterpreter` CRD installs via Helm chart\n181: - [ ] `kubectl apply -f codeinterpreter.yaml` succeeds\n182: - [ ] `kubectl get codeinterpreter` shows custom columns\n183: - [ ] Go client can create/get/update CodeInterpreter\n184: - [ ] Spec validation rejects invalid resources\n185: - [ ] Defaulting applies expected values\n186: - [ ] Code generation produces compilable client-go code\n187: \n188: ## References\n189: \n190: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n191: - [Controller Tools CRD Generation](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n192: - [Kubernetes Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n193: - Jupyter Kernel Gateway: https://jupyter-kernel-gateway.readthedocs.io/\n194: - Related: `changes/AR-001/` (AgentRuntime CRD)\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage code interpreter configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing isolated kernel environments for AI agent code execution.\n\nThe `CodeInterpreter` resource represents a configurable code execution environment with support for:\n- Multiple kernel languages (Python, R, Julia, etc.)\n- Session management and lifecycle\n- Security policies (package allowlists, operation restrictions)\n- Resource quotas (CPU, memory per session)\n- Status tracking (phase, conditions, active sessions)\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**API Group:** `codeinterpreter.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n**Kind:** `CodeInterpreter` (namespaced)  \n**Size:** S\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840991430,"end":1775840991449}}}}
