{"type":"text","timestamp":1775841006501,"sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","part":{"id":"prt_d785f4d43001pSW2Bo83qdF990","messageID":"msg_d785f450b0010uI70YCHpNr3uL","sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","type":"text","text":"Based on the existing proposal templates and the specification provided, I'll create the proposal for AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架.","time":{"start":1775841006500,"end":1775841006500}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841048209,"sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","part":{"id":"prt_d785f53a6001U3X6h0K20L0MaS","messageID":"msg_d785f450b0010uI70YCHpNr3uL","sessionID":"ses_287a1485cffe8cC5b5mQ4ByNoH","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_59b3cf2e4ac4486dab39e579","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the WorkloadManager HTTP service framework for the AgentCube platform. The WorkloadManager provides a Kubernetes-native HTTP API for managing agent runtime workloads, enabling clients to create, query, update, and delete agent runtime instances through a RESTful interface.\n\nThe WorkloadManager service provides:\n\n- **HTTP API endpoints** for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRUD operations\n- **Kubernetes client integration** using generated client-go libraries\n- **Request validation and authentication** via JWT/Kubernetes TokenReview\n- **Asynchronous operation support** with status polling\n- **Health checks and metrics** for observability\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **HTTP Server Setup** (`pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`)\n   - Gin router configuration\n   - Middleware stack (logging, recovery, CORS, auth)\n   - Graceful shutdown handling\n   - Port configuration (default :8080)\n\n2. **API Handlers** (`pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`)\n   - `agentruntime.go` — AgentRuntime CRUD endpoints\n   - `codeinterpreter.go` — CodeInterpreter CRUD endpoints\n   - `health.go` — Health check endpoints (`/healthz`, `/readyz`)\n   - `metrics.go` — Prometheus metrics endpoint\n\n3. **Request/Response Types** (`pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`)\n   - API request DTOs\n   - API response DTOs\n   - Error response format\n   - Pagination types\n\n4. **Kubernetes Client Integration** (`pkg/workloadmanager/client.go`)\n   - Clientset initialization from kubeconfig/in-cluster\n   - Informer factory setup for caching\n   - Lister usage for read operations\n\n5. **Middleware** (`pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/`)\n   - `auth.go` — JWT/Kubernetes token authentication\n   - `logging.go` — Request logging\n   - `error.go` — Centralized error handling\n   - `validation.go` — Request body validation\n\n6. **Service Interface** (`pkg/workloadmanager/service.go`)\n   - `WorkloadManager` interface definition\n   - Business logic implementation\n   - Event recording (optional)\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Controller/reconciler logic (deferred to AR-005)\n- WebSocket proxying to sandboxes (deferred to router component)\n- CLI command implementations (Python SDK task)\n- Database persistence layer (uses Kubernetes API directly)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Reason |\n|------------|------|--------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Required | HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Required | Generated Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Required | In-cluster config, rest.Config |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required | MetaV1 types, labels, fields |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Optional | JWT authentication |\n| `k8s.io/api/authentication/v1` | Optional | TokenReview for K8s auth |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Optional | Metrics export |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Python SDK**: Primary consumer of WorkloadManager HTTP API\n2. **CLI Tool**: Invokes WorkloadManager endpoints for `agentcube runtime` commands\n3. **Router**: May query WorkloadManager for routing table updates\n4. **Frontend Dashboard**: Future UI for managing agent runtimes\n5. **Controller (AR-005)**: May use WorkloadManager for status updates\n\n### Breaking Changes\n\nNone — this is the initial implementation.\n\n### Migration Path\n\nNot applicable for initial implementation. Future API version migrations will require:\n- URL path versioning (`/api/v1/`, `/api/v2/`)\n- Request/response transformers\n- Deprecation headers and warnings\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Kubernetes API Server Directly\n\n**Approach:** Clients interact directly with Kubernetes API server using client-go.\n\n**Pros:**\n- No additional service to maintain\n- Leverages K8s RBAC directly\n- Single source of truth\n\n**Cons:**\n- Exposes K8s API details to clients\n- No abstraction layer for business logic\n- Harder to add custom validation/auth\n- Clients must handle K8s-specific error codes\n- No rate limiting or throttling control\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. WorkloadManager provides necessary abstraction, custom business logic, and simplified client experience.\n\n### Alternative 2: Use controller-runtime's manager.Server\n\n**Approach:** Leverage controller-runtime's built-in HTTP server for custom endpoints.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Integrated with controller lifecycle\n- Shares manager's client and cache\n- Fewer dependencies\n\n**Cons:**\n- Less flexible than standalone Gin server\n- Tightly couples HTTP API to controller lifecycle\n- Harder to scale HTTP layer independently\n- Limited middleware ecosystem\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Standalone Gin server provides better separation of concerns and allows independent scaling of HTTP layer.\n\n### Alternative 3: gRPC instead of REST/HTTP\n\n**Approach:** Use gRPC for WorkloadManager API.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Strong typing via protobuf\n- Better performance (binary protocol)\n- Built-in streaming support\n- Auto-generated clients\n\n**Cons:**\n- Higher learning curve for consumers\n- Less debuggable (not human-readable)\n- Requires additional tooling (protoc)\n- Harder to test with curl/HTTP tools\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. REST/HTTP provides simpler integration for Python SDK and CLI, better debuggability, and aligns with Kubernetes API conventions.\n\n### Alternative 4: Use Go kit or similar framework\n\n**Approach:** Adopt Go kit for microservice architecture.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Enforces clean architecture\n- Built-in transport abstraction\n- Standardized logging/metrics\n\n**Cons:**\n- Significant boilerplate\n- Steep learning curve\n- Over-engineering for current scope\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Gin provides sufficient structure with minimal boilerplate for current needs. Can adopt Go kit patterns incrementally if complexity grows.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. **Scaffold directory structure**\n   ```\n   pkg/workloadmanager/\n   ├── server.go          # Gin server setup\n   ├── service.go         # Service interface\n   ├── client.go          # K8s client wiring\n   ├── types.go           # API types\n   ├── handlers/          # HTTP handlers\n   │   ├── agentruntime.go\n   │   ├── codeinterpreter.go\n   │   ├── health.go\n   │   └── metrics.go\n   └── middleware/        # HTTP middleware\n       ├── auth.go\n       ├── logging.go\n       └── error.go\n   ```\n\n2. **Define API types** (`types.go`)\n   - Request/response DTOs\n   - Error types\n   - Pagination types\n\n3. **Implement service interface** (`service.go`)\n   - WorkloadManager interface\n   - Concrete implementation with client-go\n\n4. **Implement handlers** (`handlers/*.go`)\n   - AgentRuntime CRUD: `POST /api/v1/agentruntimes`, `GET /api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}`, etc.\n   - CodeInterpreter CRUD: `POST /api/v1/codeinterpreters`, etc.\n   - Health checks: `GET /healthz`, `GET /readyz`\n\n5. **Implement middleware** (`middleware/*.go`)\n   - Authentication (JWT/K8s TokenReview)\n   - Logging\n   - Error handling\n\n6. **Wire up server** (`server.go`)\n   - Router configuration\n   - Middleware stack\n   - Graceful shutdown\n\n7. **Write unit tests**\n   - Handler tests with fake client-go\n   - Middleware tests\n   - Service layer tests\n\n8. **Integration tests**\n   - End-to-end API tests with test Kubernetes environment\n\n## API Specification\n\n### AgentRuntime Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes` | Create AgentRuntime |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes` | List AgentRuntimes |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get AgentRuntime |\n| `PUT` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}` | Update AgentRuntime |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n| `PATCH` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Update AgentRuntime status |\n\n### CodeInterpreter Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/codeinterpreters` | List CodeInterpreters |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n| `PUT` | `/api/v1/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Update CodeInterpreter |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/v1/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n\n### Health Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/healthz` | Liveness probe |\n| `GET` | `/readyz` | Readiness probe |\n| `GET` | `/metrics` | Prometheus metrics |\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] WorkloadManager server starts and listens on configured port\n- [ ] All CRUD endpoints return correct responses\n- [ ] Authentication middleware validates JWT/K8s tokens\n- [ ] Fake client-go enables unit testing without K8s cluster\n- [ ] Health endpoints return 200 OK\n- [ ] Metrics endpoint exposes Prometheus-format metrics\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown completes within 30 seconds\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with test K8s cluster\n\n## References\n\n- [Gin Web Framework](https://gin-gonic.com/)\n- [Kubernetes client-go](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go)\n- Related: `deployment/client-go.md`\n- Related: `changes/AR-001/` (AgentRuntime CRD)\n- Related: `changes/AR-002/` (CodeInterpreter CRD)\n- Related: `changes/AR-003/` (Shared Types)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841048194,"end":1775841048205}}}}
